The paper deals with the problem of interference management in MIMO systems operating in the lower part of the millimeter-wave spectrum band, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), millimeter-wave communication (cs.MM), and communication systems (cs.COM). The focus on interference management and sum-rate maximization suggests that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.COM.
